long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
üîç Fast Advanced Google Search. Find the results you need fast! üöÄ

Improve productivity & find what you're looking for on Google quickly by filtering search results with advanced Google search operators.

Optimize your search query effortlessly with advanced Google search operators using this convenient Google search assistant tool. Say goodbye to the hassle of cheat sheets!

‚≠ê Site search - Search by the current site or domain - autofill feature

‚≠ê Query by file type

‚≠ê Query by Date range

‚≠ê Find Keywords within the Page title, Body and URL of websites

‚≠ê Query by country & language

‚≠ê Exclude/filter out keywords

‚≠ê Shortcut Alt + G to open the search tool

‚≠ê Perform complex Google search query quickly

‚≠ê Order search parameters by Dragging to best suit your use case

‚≠ê Enable & Disable cards to show only the relevant search parameters 

‚≠ê Open a new tab or use the current tab option

‚≠ê OSINT open source intelligence investigations tool

‚≠ê Custom search experience

‚≠ê Remove query parameters you don't need quickly by clicking the bin icon and removing multiple search cards, so you can focus on the filters that matter most to you. 

Supported query operators/parameters
 ‚ñ∏ Exclude - multiple exclude using space separator
 ‚ñ∏ Site search - search current site or search domain - includes use current domain button that will populate the field for you
 ‚ñ∏ File type - filter by any file type e.g. pdf, docx, txt, xls, ppt etc
 ‚ñ∏ Search type - websites, images, video etc
 ‚ñ∏ Keywords within - Any, Page title, Body and URL
 ‚ñ∏ Date Range - Before/After
 ‚ñ∏ Date Range quick (Max Age of result)
 ‚ñ∏ View Google's cache of a website
 ‚ñ∏ Turn off Google personalised search results
 ‚ñ∏ Sites that contain link specified
 ‚ñ∏ Related site search
 ‚ñ∏ Turn off safe search
 ‚ñ∏ Country support - see search results based on country
 ‚ñ∏ Search by Language

Customise your Advanced Google search experience and improve the quality of your search results. Perform SEO research techniques quickly using this Google advanced search power tool with the available search utilities.

 ‚≠ê Find when google last indexed a website with the cache parameter

 ‚≠ê Discover hidden opportunities for internal linking by searching for phrases in your domain or website.

 ‚≠ê Conduct competitor SEO research, just use the "related sites" search operator followed by a website URL. 

Permissions: The tabs permission is necessary for the populate domain and page buttons.

Get in touch! Have an idea or feature request? Contact us, feedback is always welcome! 
Twitter: @PartialOverload
